args: Urk! ...Heh. Oh, I'm not done yet.\nLet's see what you think of THIS!
Y-yeah, I'm fine. Just twisted my ankle.
But I lost again, which is SO annoying!
But you've won ten and lost ten,\nso we're actually tied.
Unacceptable! Today was going to be the\nday I finally had more wins than losses!
We can't stop like this.\nC'mon, let's go! Again!
I told you this was going to happen.\nYou need to take a break.
Yeah, okay. Maybe you're right. But once\nI'm better, we're going again!
I'm bummed I didn't win, but I'm also\nreally happy.
When I don't win every single time,\nit means I'm fighting someone strong.
And fighting strong people makes ME\nstrong, which in turns makes me happy.
What, do I have something on my face?\n...Is it blood? That happens a lot.
I was just wondering why you're\nso fixated on getting stronger.
Er, is that even a real question?
I mean, what's your endgame?\nWhy is this so important to you?
Why? Because I want to get stronger\nso I can BE stronger! You don't need\nmore reason than that.
But you must have something\nDRIVING you toward that goal.
Well, okay, that's not TOTALLY true.\nI guess I'm trying to do this because\nI want to be more like my master.
He's a member of the Qilin tribe, right?
Yep. He and the rest of the tribe raised\nme from the time I was a small child.
The Qilin are said to be a mysterious\npeople who possess mystic powers\nand knowledge.
Oh, they're the bee's knees, all right!
They're the successors to an ancient\ncivilization, and they know things no\none else does ANYWHERE.
Yet they live in harsh environments,\nwithout concern for wealth or fame.
In truth, it's their strong HEARTS\nthat are the most impressive thing.
Anyways, I guess I'm aiming to have\na heart like theirs someday.
You clearly have a lot of respect for them.
I guess you could say they're role models.\nI mean, my master is, of course, but so is\neveryone else from the tribe.
Anyway, you wanted to know why I'm\ndoing all this, so now you do.
My master always used to say,\n＂Just keep striving for greater heights.＂
That's why I need to grow stronger.
(I'm trying to be stronger so I can protect\nwhat is important to me.)
(But I'm not sure Lin You's reason is\nactually reason enough...)
